video.title: Little Princess
video.synopsis: Based on the best-selling children's books by author-illustrator Tony Ross, this animated series follows the curious and charming Little Princess.

episodes.synopsis: One of Little Princess's lovely white teeth falls out -- just before the royal family photograph!
episodes.title: I Want My Tooth

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is not happy with everyone doing everything for her. But when she decides to go it alone, things don't turn out to be quite so easy.
episodes.title: I Don't Want Help

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess really isn't ready to go to bed. Why should she have to sleep when everyone else is wide awake?!
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Go to Bed

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess can't decide what she wants to be when she grows up. So, with the help of her friends, she sets about trying lots of different jobs.
episodes.title: I Don't Know What to Be

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess discovers that everyone in the kingdom can whistle except her, she sets about finding her own special noise.
episodes.title: I Want to Whistle

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess doesn't want to give up her dummy, and when it starts mysteriously disappearing, she's determined to get it back!
episodes.title: I Want My Dummy

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess loses things that her friends have lent her, she sets out to try to remember just what she did with them.
episodes.title: I Can't Remember

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess does not like baths. In fact, she'll do anything to avoid them. But it's soon clear that she'll have to have a bath sooner or later.
episodes.title: I Don't Want a Bath

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess gets into trouble, she just doesn't know whether to own up or let poor old Scruff take the blame.
episodes.title: I Didn't Do It

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess hates having her hair combed, but she discovers it's a lot more fun combing other people's hair.
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Comb My Hair

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess grows her own tomato plant, she discovers that tomatoes can actually be a lot of fun.
episodes.title: I Don't Like Salad

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess decides to learn some magic tricks for a show. But she's soon in for a shock when the magic works a bit too well.
episodes.title: I Want to Do Magic

episodes.synopsis: Things get tricky for Little Princess when the mess in her room gets out of hand and teddy bear Gilbert suddenly goes missing.
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Tidy Up

episodes.synopsis: When a new music box arrives at the castle and captures everyone's attention, Little Princess decides she should play an instrument too.
episodes.title: I Want a Trumpet

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess gets a new paddling pool to play in, she discovers that playing by herself isn't quite as much fun as sharing.
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Share

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess loves playing in the mud. But when she discovers a slimy worm, the fun stops. Either she or the worm is going to have to leave.
episodes.title: I Don't Like Worms

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess loses her voice, she has to find a new way to make herself heard. Before long, everyone wants her to get her voice back!
episodes.title: I Want My Voice Back

episodes.synopsis: When teddy Gilbert's leg falls off, Little Princess is very upset. So while he rests, she sets off to find a playmate to take his place.
episodes.title: What's Wrong With Gilbert?

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess tries to make the perfect tent, things don't go according to plan. But if at first you don't succeed, try, try again.
episodes.title: I Want My Tent

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess decides she is going to win all the games she plays. But she's in for a bit of a shock when someone finally stops her winning streak.
episodes.title: I Want to Win

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess has a cold, and she's not happy about it. But a runny nose won't stop her having fun -- even if she has to bend the rules a little.
episodes.title: I Don't Want a Cold

episodes.synopsis: When Maid has her day off, Little Princess decides to look after things at the castle for Maid while she's gone.
episodes.title: Maid's Day Off?

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess finds a tadpole and soon discovers that wild animals don't make the easiest of pets.
episodes.title: Can I Keep It?

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess decides to bake the General a birthday cake. But Chef had the same idea. Will the castle kitchen be big enough for the both of them?
episodes.title: I Want to Cook

episodes.synopsis: When the leaves start falling off the trees and reveal the Little Princess's secret summer hiding spot, she decides she's going to stop autumn.
episodes.title: I Don't Like Autumn

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is not happy when she discovers she has head lice -- and the rest of the members of the household are trying to avoid her.
episodes.title: I Don't Want Nits

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess gets a lovely pair of new, sparkly shoes, and she really doesn't want to take them off.
episodes.title: I Want My New Shoes

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess's pet snail Speedy dies, she decides to give him a proper funeral so that she and the household can say goodbye to a good friend.
episodes.title: I Want My Snail

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is getting bigger and can't fit into her favorite clothes anymore. But that doesn't mean she's ready to give them up just yet.
episodes.title: But They're Mine!

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess wants a brand-new shiny sledge to play on. But when she finally gets one, she realizes that "new" doesn't always mean better.
episodes.title: I Want My Sledge

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess's new shop in the castle is a big hit, until her customers discover that the merchandise she's gathered all belongs to someone else.
episodes.title: I Want a Shop

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess decides to run all the races herself when she's stuck with Scruff and the Admiral on her team for Sports Day.
episodes.title: It's Sports Day!

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess loves pirates and decides to become one herself, but she soon learns that it's not as much fun as she imagined.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Pirate

episodes.synopsis: When she hurts her foot on the way to the fair, Little Princess gets stuck at the castle. Luckily, the queen knows how to cheer her up.
episodes.title: I Want to Go to the Fair

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess just has to win the prize for best costume at the fancy dress party, but each of her outfits is a bigger disaster that the last!
episodes.title: I Want to Dress Up

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess just has to know what surprise gift is in store for her upcoming birthday, so she sets out to find its hiding place.
episodes.title: I Want a Surprise

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess's tricycle is just too slow and she decides it's time for a two-wheeler. But riding a bicycle isn't as easy as it seems.
episodes.title: I Want a Bicycle

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess hides when she overhears her parents talking about her. Are they really going to send her away, or did she misunderstand?
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Leave Home

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is the only one in the castle without a best friend, so she decides her baby cousin would be perfect for the job.
episodes.title: I Want a Best Friend

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess isn't looking forward to Great Aunty's visit because she always has to give her a kiss. Is there a way to avoid the awful greeting?
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Kiss Great Aunty

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess prepares all the ingredients for the perfect midnight feast, but will she be able to stay awake long enough to enjoy it?
episodes.title: I Want a Midnight Feast

episodes.synopsis: When she's sent to the Naughty Step, Little Princess must be good for the rest of the day if she wants to help decorate the Christmas tree.
episodes.title: I Want to Be Good

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess's new crayons are so perfect and clean that she doesn't want to use them. So who's taking them out of the box when she's not around?
episodes.title: I Want My Crayons

episodes.synopsis: Frustrated with not being able to reach everything, Little Princess decides to find a way to be taller, but nothing seems to work.
episodes.title: I Want to Be Tall

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess gets a plaster cast on her leg, her bravery inspires the General when he needs a cast on his own leg.
episodes.title: I Want My Plaster

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess breaks the rules and plays on her new swing without an adult around. When she falls off, who will be there to help her up again?
episodes.title: I Want My Swing

episodes.synopsis: Jealous of all the attention everyone's giving her baby cousin, Little Princess decides to try becoming a baby herself.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Baby

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess spends a day living in the garden shed as a cavegirl, but her primitive new life grows a little scary when night falls.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Cavegirl

episodes.synopsis: When she decides to put on a puppet show, Little Princess finds that getting things ready for the audience can be just as tricky as performing.
episodes.title: I Want My Puppets

episodes.synopsis: The queen can't help trying to figure out what Little Princess is giving her for Mother's Day, but even the princess isn't sure what it is.
episodes.title: Mother's Day!

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess discovers that her great-grandfather was an explorer, but she finds following his trail to Blue Boogaloo Land almost impossible.
episodes.title: I Want to Be an Explorer

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess admires the collections of everyone else in the castle, but she finds that starting one of her own isn't as easy as it looks.
episodes.title: I Want to Collect

episodes.synopsis: When she exchanges roles with her mother for the day, Little Princess soon discovers how hard it can be to be queen.
episodes.title: I Want to Be Queen

episodes.synopsis: When a rainy day keeps her stuck in the castle, Little Princess is bored until she finds her football, which isn't the best toy for playing indoors.
episodes.title: I Want to Play Football

episodes.synopsis: No one in the castle wants to go play in the rain with Little Princess. After a few mishaps, she begins to understand why.
episodes.title: I Want to Play in the Rain

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess puts together a show for Great Aunty's visit, but everything starts to fall apart during the rehearsal.
episodes.title: I Want to Do a Show

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess doesn't want to attend dance class, where they make her dance like a butterfly. But is she missing out on all the fun?
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Dance

episodes.synopsis: A postcard from Great Aunty gives Little Pirincess the idea of traveling, but will going on holiday alone be any fun?
episodes.title: I Want to Go On Holiday

episodes.synopsis: When Little Princess finds a sheep on the castle grounds, she makes him her new best friend, unaware that he belongs to someone else.
episodes.title: I Want My Sheep

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is always late when something fun happens at the castle, so she hatches a plan to make sure she never misses out again.
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Miss It

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess tastes baked beans for the first time, and now she can't get enough. But is it possible to have too much of your favorite thing?
episodes.title: I Want Baked Beans

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess lends her favorite teddy bear, Gilbert, to her baby cousin who's come to visit. But when it's time to go, will she get Gilbert back?
episodes.title: Can I Have It Back Now, Please?

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is the only one in the castle who knows the General's secret, and she's having a hard time keeping it to herself.
episodes.title: I Can Keep a Secret

episodes.synopsis: Nothing can scare Little Princess -- except maybe the approaching thunderstorm. But can she be brave enough to rescue Scruff, who's stranded outside?
episodes.title: I Don't Like Thunderstorms

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess didn't find any chocolate at the treasure hunt last year, but this year she's found a map that will help her win.
episodes.title: I Want to Find the Treasure

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is delighted when Great Uncle Walter's Shetland pony, Horace, comes to stay -- until she discovers how stubborn he is.
episodes.title: I Want My Horace

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess watches an old slide show of the king and queen's wedding and decides that she wants to be a bridesmaid.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Bridesmaid

episodes.synopsis: A power cut hits the castle as the household is preparing a birthday party for Great-Uncle Walter. Can the celebration go ahead without electricity?
episodes.title: Who Turned the Lights Off?

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess, Algie and Maid compete to see who can build the best tree house.
episodes.title: I Want My Treehouse

episodes.synopsis: Princess wants to be a vet, but looking after sick animals isn't easy -- and the animals don't seem that keen on being treated.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Vet

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess ruins the brand-new dress given to her by Great Aunty when she plays with the scissors and glue without permission.
episodes.title: I Want to Cut Out

episodes.synopsis: Algie visits the castle and is soon showing Princess how well he can train her dog, Scruff. Does Scruff really prefer Algie?
episodes.title: I Want Scruff

episodes.synopsis: Princess is learning to roller skate, but it's not easy and she's tempted to give up; however, she decides to keep on trying with her dad.
episodes.title: I Want to Skate

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess and her friends are off to the seaside but are disappointed to find the beach empty, and worse still, it's raining.
episodes.title: I Want to Go to the Seaside

episodes.synopsis: When a flock of unfriendly geese drives Admiral from his pond, Little Princess sets about finding a new role for him in the castle.
episodes.title: Please Don't Go

episodes.synopsis: When Scruff finds three little duck eggs, Princess must look after the eggs, which soon hatch into three very hungry and playful ducklings.
episodes.title: I Want My Duck

episodes.synopsis: Princess is determined to win the golden rosette at the castle's annual pet talent contest but is not sure that Puss has what it takes to win.
episodes.title: I'm Going to Win the Rosette

episodes.synopsis: After General and Maid have an argument, Little Princess tries to help them be friends again.
episodes.title: I Don't Like Arguments

episodes.synopsis: There is a singing competition in the kingdom and everyone is entering. Little Princess is determined to win, but what song will she sing?
episodes.title: I Want to Sing

episodes.synopsis: Algie keeps playing tricks on Princess, so she decides that it's time to get back at him. But playing a joke on someone isn't as easy as she thought.
episodes.title: I Want to Play a Joke

episodes.synopsis: After someone eats all Princess's freshly baked biscuits, like a true detective, she sets up a number of traps to catch the hungry thief.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Detective

episodes.synopsis: Princess is bird-watching, but wild birds aren't easy to spot when they keep flying off if they see or hear her. How can she get a closer look?
episodes.title: I Want My Robin

episodes.synopsis: When General organizes a gymkhana, Princess is sure that she and Horace are the perfect team. But can they win against Algie and his bicycle?
episodes.title: I Want a Gymkhana

episodes.synopsis: General wants to be strong so that he can impress Maid, and Little Princess is determined to help.
episodes.title: I Want to Be Strong

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is very excited when Aunty arrives at the castle with a piano, but learning to play involves a lot of hard work and practice.
episodes.title: I Don't Want to Play the Piano

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess is leaving home to go to space, but despite all the stars and aliens, she soon realizes that her home is just as exciting.
episodes.title: I Want to Go to Space

episodes.synopsis: Princess does not like rules and decides to become a police officer so that everyone else in the castle has to follow the same rules she's given.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Policeman

episodes.synopsis: Princess is delighted when everyone is locked out of the castle, as it means they will have to spend the night camping.
episodes.title: I Want to Go Camping

episodes.synopsis: Realizing the importance of not wasting things, Princess must think of ways to recycle all the old rubbish she has saved from being thrown out.
episodes.title: I Want to Recycle

episodes.synopsis: Maid is not very well, which is good news for nurse Princess because she's been looking for a patient to care for.
episodes.title: I Want to Be a Nurse

episodes.synopsis: Princess never wins at hide-and-seek. That is, until she finds a hidden room in the castle, which she decides to keep secret from the household.
episodes.title: I Want to Play Hide and Seek

episodes.synopsis: Princess wants to redecorate her bedroom but cannot make up her mind what color to paint it.
episodes.title: I Want a New Bedroom

episodes.synopsis: Princess is delighted when Scruff finds a lost tiara, until she discovers it belongs to Maid. Will Rachel keep it or return it to the rightful owner?
episodes.title: I Want Your Tiara

episodes.synopsis: Princess wants to become famous for doing lots of wonderful things so that she can have a statue made in her honor, just like her Great-Uncle Walter.
episodes.title: I Want to Be Famous

episodes.synopsis: While having a sleepover at the castle, Princess persuades Algie to join her on a nighttime dragon hunt.
episodes.title: I Want a Sleepover

episodes.synopsis: Princess tells Algie she's an ace ice skater, but when everyone comes to watch her, she must decide whether to admit that she exaggerated her skills.
episodes.title: I Want to Ice Skate

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess wants to receive a letter in the post, but she needs to find someone to write to first. How will she find herself a pen pal?
episodes.title: I Want a Penpal

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess and Great-Uncle Walter team up for the castle go-cart race.
episodes.title: I Want a Go Kart

episodes.synopsis: Little Princess has opened her own café with Algie as her waiter, but Algie does not like being told what to do.
episodes.title: I Mustn't Be Bossy

episodes.synopsis: Princess is looking after Sticky, Great-Uncle Walter's stick insect, but Sticky does not always stay where he is supposed to.
episodes.title: I Want a Stick Insect
